CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 30, 1961, pg. B2, reads: "Tigers Are 'Y' Champions - The Tigers won the Centre Avenue YMCA Softball League title by defeating the Bears, 19-5. The Tigers displayed championship form behind the hard hitting of William Parker, Ronald Major and Anthony Fountain. Above the Tigers' team, retrieving the trophy. It is being presented to the team captain, Ronald Major, by Paul M, Dykes, youth secretary to the 'Y.' Looking on, left to right, are George Pitts, Alton Allesberry, William Parker, Fred Hodges, Ederick Todman and Ronald Twyman."
TitMainTitle: Paul M. Dykes presenting trophy to Tigers softball captain Ronald Major, surrounded by teammates, including Anthony "Tony" Fountain Sr. on left, George Pitts, Alton Allesberry, William Parker, Fred Hodges, Ederick Todman, and Ronald Twyman in Centre Avenue YMCA
